# Avocado Phenology Classification — Objective 1

This repository contains a fully reproducible pipeline for **Objective 1** of the avocado phenology project:  
**classifying avocado phenological stages using CART models trained on harmonized Landsat–Sentinel (HLS) vegetation indices.**

The workflow is implemented as a sequence of R scripts that load, align, engineer, model, evaluate, and visualize phenology classification results.

---

## 📌 Pipeline Overview

The workflow consists of six scripts:

| Step | Script | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| 1 | `01_load_data.R` | Load raw HLS vegetation index data and phenology reference tables |
| 2 | `02_align_phenology.R` | Expand phenology windows and align with satellite observations |
| 3 | `03_feature_engineering.R` | Prepare modelling dataset (predictors + response) |
| 4 | `06_cart_models.R` | Train CART models (combined + county‑specific) |
| 5 | `08_cart_confusion_matrices.R` | Evaluate model accuracy, kappa, and class‑wise performance |
| 6 | `09_plot_cart_trees.R` | Export publication‑quality CART tree diagrams |

All scripts run top‑to‑bottom and produce outputs stored in `data_clean/` and `figures/`.

